title: IntroductionPostTutorial
---
{$mentorName}: “Welcome to the Royal Blacksmith Guild, apprentice. There are expectations with the job, so I’ll help you out as your senior on what you need to do.”
{$mentorName}: “As you already know, being a Royal Blacksmith is far different than any regular blacksmithing job. We work with a rare metal not available to the public.”
{$mentorName}: “It is our work with Pleiotium that holds us in such high status. And what we make with it can change the pages of history depending on how it’s handled.”
{$mentorName}: “But such a special title is often sought out by nobles desiring glory or status, so sometimes we end up with foolish apprentices like the one we saw back there. Now I ask you, because I don’t know you, what type of royal blacksmith do you hope to be?”
{$playerName}: “I wish to be the one talked about in history, sir.”
{$mentorName}: “Aye, that’s good to hear. Now, some advice, I suggest that you start trying to build some connections out there. Most apprentices hole themselves in their forge, but lose sight of the most important things about smithing. The commissioners themselves.” 
{$mentorName}: “To stop being merely an apprentice and become an official Royal Blacksmith, you are going to need someone who brings out the best of your craft. Carefully consider what you want out of your work, and what commissions feel right to you.”
{$playerName}: “Thank you, I’ll make sure to remember that.”
{$mentorName}: “Good. Now, with that said, your first task here should be preparing your own personal forge. Organize and restock on what resources you will need for your work.”
{$mentorName}: “Once you're done with that, go check the commission board near closing hours to see if anything sounds good to you. You’ll find requests for possible projects there.” 
{$mentorName}: “I’ll be at my own forge if you have any more questions, so I’ll take my leave first. Get to work, apprentice.” 
{$playerName}: “Wait! Before you go, could I get your name?”
<<set $mentorName to "Isham">>
{$mentorName}: “It’s not much, but you can call me Isham. I’m one of the head Royal Blacksmiths here. Now get going before you fall behind.
{$playerName}: “Yes, sir!”
The day passes by quickly, with work on your forge seeming endless. Finally, you manage to clean the old forge up to your liking. 
The only thing left to do now is to restock fuel for your furnace from the coal bunker. 
As you load a crate full of coal, you realize how heavy it is to carry. Still, you decide to try to carry it all in one trip. 
An official Royal Blacksmith needs to be strong for their work. That notion pushes you to make a reckless decision.
//<<change_background "hallway">>
{$playerName}: Just…a bit…further…
The crate of coal, filled to the brim, blocks your field of view as you trudge through the hallway. 
Suddenly, just as you think you might be reaching the end, you collide with something heavy in front of you with a large thud. 
Falling onto your back in surprise, the crate of coal that was in your hands lands onto the floor, its contents spilling all over the place.
{$redFlagName}: “Oh dear, I’m so sorry. Are you alright?”
Looking up, you are met with a gentle, smooth hand stemming from what could only be described as both a stunningly gorgeous and odd woman. 
Donning elegant clothing and jewelry, her status was apparent to any perceiver. She would have looked like any regular, wealthy client the guild often gets if it weren’t for her eyes.
<<set $redFlagName to "Wealthy Woman">>
Staring right through you, her pupils devoid of warmth watch your every movement with an intense gaze. Her crimson irises remain firm, refusing to blink until you take her hand.   
A part of you finds them to be entrancing. The other terrifying. 
{$redFlagName}: “Is something the matter?”
{$playerName}: “Oh, no, nothing’s wrong. Thank you.”
Taking her hand, you snap out of your thoughts as you stand back up. You notice her clothes have become stained from the coal.
{$playerName}: “I’m so sorry, I wasn’t watching where I was going. Do you need me to wash that for you, ma’am?”
{$redFlagName}: Oh, this? No, it’s fine. In fact, how about I help you pick up this mess? You look like you need it. 
-> “No, I can do this myself.”
    <<change_affinity "red flag" 1>>
    {$redFlagName}: “Ah, a tough [guy/girl/one], I see. No need to worry, dear, I don’t mind getting a bit dirty now and then.”
    {$playerName}: “Really, it’s fin—”
    {$redFlagName}: “Too late! I made up my mind.” 
    Already on her knees, the woman looks up to you with a mischievous grin as she picks up the coal. 
    {$playerName}: “Ah…what the hell, let’s just get this picked up quick.”
-> “Should you even be here?”
