{$redFlagName}: “Let me help you carry this so you don’t go bumping into any more people. And this time I’m not taking no for an answer.”
Before you could respond, the lady had already placed her hands on the other side of a crate. Deciding it's best not to argue any longer, you go along with her whims until you reach your forge.
<<change_background "personal forge">>
{$redFlagName}: “I’ve never seen a royal forge before. I always thought it would look more…impressive?”
{$playerName}: “Well, I am only an apprentice. I don’t imagine they give those fancy ones to just about anyone.”
{$redFlagName}: “Don’t sell yourself short. I see in you the potential to become a great Royal Blacksmith.”
{$playerName}: “And how would you know that?”
{$redFlagName}: “My trading company has collaborated before with the Royal Blacksmiths, and I would say you remind me just of them.”
{$playerName}: “That is?”
{$redFlagName}: “You have the eyes of someone with ambition. That look where you will do anything to become the best at what you do. I like that about you.”
{$playerName}: “I never thought that way about myself. Do I really like that to others?”
{$redFlagName}: “Hmmm…I wouldn’t know. I wouldn’t call myself exactly normal, anyway, so you probably don’t have to worry about others seeing that part of you.”
{$playerName}: “That’s a relief. Oh! I forgot to say, but thank you for the help. Would you mind if I were to ask for your name?”
