{$playerName}: “It’s nice to meet you, too, {$redFlagName}.”
You exchange goodbyes with the odd lady who had left just as swiftly as she entered. It was only after you had returned to work, however, that you remembered something important. 
You had not once given her your name.  
You feel a shiver roll down your spine as you finish loading the coal into the furnace. You could only hope that she had learned your name through some reasonable way.
After a few more long hours of hard work, you wipe off the last of your sweat as you finish completing your forge. All that remains is to obtain the Pleiotium and find a worthwhile commission.
You remember your senior’s words about how it would be a good idea to look at the commission board for possible requests. You decide that, with nothing else left to do for today, you would give it a look before the guild closes.
<<change_background "commissions room nighttime">>
Leaving your forge, you enter the Commission's room within the guild. Here, commissions from customers unable to personally request a Royal Blacksmith are instead placed onto a guild board for apprentices to view. 
The guild will require apprentices to choose from among these requests to complete. Once chosen, an apprentice is obligated to fulfill the request in an allotted time unless there is an exemption to be made.
The guild will then judge the apprentice's work and the customer’s review to determine their skillset. If judged high enough to be at the skill level of a Royal Blacksmith, the apprentice will have the opportunity to take the Royal Blacksmith Exam for promotion. 
Walking up to the commission board, you look at the handful of requests pinned to it, littered with a wide variety of trinkets requested. Most of them are simple designs that don’t pique your attention, while others seem long, tedious, and lackluster to do. 
But one among them stands out to you. A morningstar, one with a blueprint attached to the request so intricately designed that you can’t help but be drawn to it.
When you read the name of the commissioner, however, your excitement instantly drops. 
{$playerName}: [i]{$redFlagName}...of course she would request something as odd as this.[/i]
Reading more into the peculiar request she made, you do not notice the noise of a door opening behind you.
{$bestFriendName}: “...what am…doing wrong…”
You turn backwards, startled by the quiet grumbling voice. 
